    {
      "@id": "./",
      "@type": "Dataset",
      "name": "DIGIBAT Discovery Benchmark",
      "description": "<h2>DIGIBAT Discovery Benchmark</h2><p>A reference dataset comprising ~250 lithium-ion coin cells systematically fabricated via automated assembly equipment at <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.imperial.ac.uk/digibat/\">DIGIBAT</a> facility. Designed to span common cathode/anode/electrolyte chemistries, as a shared benchmark for battery-informatics tooling.</p><h3>Characterisation</h3><p>The dataset is designed as a dual-layer knowledge graph that cleanly segregates precursor material characterisation from the final electrochemical cell performance:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Precursor-level characterisation:</strong> Microstructural, morphological, and chemical properties—including SEM/TEM, XRD, and XPS are mapped directly to individual electrode precursor records (e.g., <code>P025-ELD-001</code>) rather than individual cells.</p></li><li><p><strong>Cell-level characterisation:</strong> In-situ and operational testing data—such as Neware cycling exports (<code>.xlsx</code>) and BioLogic CV/EIS data (<code>.mpr</code>)—are anchored directly to the respective coin cell entry (e.g., <code>P025-CEL-001</code>).</p></li><li><p><strong>Visual records:</strong> Raw cell assembly photos are attached directly to each cell record. (Note: electrode alignment images are only available for cell batches built using the <code>EQP-D02-Cellerate</code>).</p></li></ul><h3>Mass-correction note</h3><p>The original charge/discharge capacities recorded in cell-side files used the total electrode disc mass (e.g. 23 mg) rather than the active material mass after subtracting current collector foil (e.g. 20 mg). Capacities have been recalculated; the corrected nominal capacity is shown on each cell record as <code>characteristic_mass</code> / <code>nominal_voltage</code>. Some cells turn out to be limited on the carbon side after recalculation — for those the nominal capacity is taken as <code>min(cathode, anode)</code>. The per-file raw capacity values in the cycling exports are therefore <em>stale</em>; the cell-record value is the source of truth.</p><h3>Infrastructure &amp; Funding</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Ingestion Pipeline:</strong> The ingestion code that produced this collection is acessible on <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://github.com/datalab-industries/digibat-datalab-deployment/tree/main/scripts/discovery_benchmark\">Github</a></p></li><li><p><strong>Sponsorship:</strong> This campaign to generate open, multimodal battery datasets for the research community is supported by the <strong>Henry Royce Institute</strong>, <strong>UK Research and Innovation (UKRI)</strong>, and <strong>Department for Science, Innovation & Technology</strong> through UKRI.</p></li></ul><h3>Project Contributions &amp; Framework</h3><p>A collaborative milestone involving the multi-disciplinary deployment of laboratory automation, data engineering, and informatics tools:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Data Creators:</strong> Dr Rob Hunter, Dr Niamh Hartley</p></li><li><p><strong>Data Curators:</strong> Dr Matthew Evans (datalab integration), Dr Lucas Garcia Verga (Data architecture), Dr Felix Mildner (BattINFO annotation, DigiBOT creator), Dr Ben Smith (datalab systems), Shirley Xiong (CellSeer visualisation)</p></li><li><p><strong>Project Manager:</strong> Dr Jingyu Feng</p></li><li><p><strong>Project Leaders:</strong> Prof Magda Titirici, Prof Aron Walsh, Prof Sam Cooper</p></li></ul><p></p>",
